
            cclive installation

Normally "./configure" followed by "make install". See "./configure --help"
for more info.


            Optional packages

--enable-sigwinch (default)
    If enabled, cclive handles SIGWINCH signal to resize with terminal
    width. Known to work on BSD/Linux, if you are using another OS
    you may want to use --disable-sigwinch.

--with-man (default)
    Whether the manual page should be installed. --without-man disables
    this.

--with-perl
    If enabled, cclive builds with embedded Perl interpreter. This is
    currently used for parsing video page <title> tags. This enables the
    use of the --title and the --title-cclass options.
    
    Note that you will also need the HTML::Tokenizer Perl module.


            Prerequisites

 - libcurl (7.18.0+)

Optional:
 - Perl 5.8+ with HTML::TokeParser module. See --with-perl above.


            Examples

 # ./configure --prefix=/usr/local --without-sigwinch
 # make install
